> Published in  Stephen Little: Taoism and the Arts of China. Chicago: The Art Institute of Chicago, 2000: 364
===Pine in Japanese Painting===
* Fujimoto Tesseki 藤本鉄石 (1817-1863): Oimatsu zu 老松図 (Old Pine). Hanging scroll, 1859, ink on satin, 148x51.6cm, Terry Welch Collection at Honolulu Academy of Arts.
> Published in Paul Berry and Michiyo Morioka: Literati Modern, bujinga from late Edo to twentieth century Japan, Seattle: University of Washington Press, 2008: 198-199.

